5:
Oohh... the present exchange is
finally happening tomorrow!
7:
Nobody ever died from exchanging
presents, right? This should be okay!
10:
Though I can't help but feel kind of...
restless.
14:
Hey you... Are you the dancer,
Roselia?
22:
Oh, you're one of those pirates from
before, aren't you. Sorry, you're
gonna have to do better than that if
you—
30:
That's a lot more people than I was
expecting. This is hardly fair.
32:
You could have at least stayed
dead 'n spared us all the work of
doing this, you know.
34:
When I heard you had survived, I
nearly popped a blood vessel! This
time, we'll finish you for good.
36:
Don't worry, you can rest at ease—I
won't be using bombs this time
around!
40:
It's getting a bit cliché, you know? I
want to try out some new material.
42:
Material? I have no idea what you're
talking about!
44:
I won't be satisfied until I dump your
corpse overboard myself!
Rip her to pieces, men!
46:
Being ripped to pieces doesn't like a
fun way to go...
56:
Death is gonna have to wait just a
little while longer.
I've got more living to do.
57:
How can I go and die today? Who
knows what incredible things
tomorrow has in store for me!
60:
Oh shut up and die already!
Do you have any idea how many of
my men you've cut down?!
62:
I'm gonna be honest—I don't quite
remember. As many men as jobs
I've taken on? That's my best guess.
65:
The sooner you shut your mouth, the
better!
67:
In my experience, she's not one for
stayin' quiet.
72: This is actually her on a good day.
82:
I'm a bit spent, I won't lie!
Think I could leave the rest to you?
85:
Don't worry, we're on this.
Be careful!
90:
Well, it was a pleasure chatting with
you, Mr. Pirate!
99:
Are you hurt, Roselia? Why would
you go and do something so
reckless...
103:
Haha, I had a feeling I was gonna
get a ribbing for this one.
104:
But this time I actually tried to stay
alive! That has to count for
something.
108:
Yes, that's a marked improvement,
but... You still need to be more
careful.
114:
I'm not sure if this present'll be to
your liking, but...
118:
I will treasure it.
I hope you treasure your present,
too.
128:
You still haven't learned your lesson,
huh? Not even after your last
encounter with this lot?
131:
I guess I haven't. But I can't just sit
still and do nothing, you know? Too
much peace just makes me...
restless.
132:
Plus, if I just up and quit, what'll
happen to all my clients? All those
people out there who have a score
they need to settle. Who's gonna
help them?
135:
But you made a promise, didn't you?
Not to die.
138:
Which is why I've brought you along,
silly. So I can finish my jobs without
getting killed!
140:
Not a word about this to Light, you
hear?
145:
Oh, don't worry. We're only taking
out bad guys here! I'm sure Light
would understand.
154:
It's good to have some excitement
in your day—it helps tomorrow feel
even more fresh! Come on, Nimbus.
Let's dance!
159: Heh. Don't mind if I do.
